<article id="faq-directory">
    <h2>Directory</h2>

    <h3>What all does the basic search look for?</h3>
    <p>
        The basic search checks the same categories as the advanced search except
        it checks if the key term matches any record in those categories.
        For example, if you enter "computer", the directory returns all alumni
        with "computer" in their first name, last name, major, graduation year,
        job category, job title, or employer.
    </p>

    <h3>How is the advanced search different from the basic search?</h3>
    <p>
        The advanced search returns all alumni that match each of the criteria
        given. The blank categories are ignored. For example, if you want to
        search for someone who has a job in finance but not necessarily those
        who got a degree in finance, then you could enter "finance" in the job
        category field to search for alumni with a finance job, which might
        include business, economics, or any other major. 
    </p>

    <h3>Are the searches case sensative?</h3>
    <p>
        No. Capitalization doesn't matter.
    </p>

    <h3>How do you search for graduation year?</h3>
    <p>
        The directory returns all the alumni that have a graduation year that
        contains the digits you provide. For example, if you enter "20", then
        the directory would return all the alumni that graduated in the 21st
        century and those that have a "20" in their graduation year such as
        19<b>20</b> or 2<b>20</b>1 in the future.
    </p>
</article>

